(10, 'Chicken curry', 'Chicken curry is a savory dish featuring tender pieces of chicken cooked in a fragrant blend of spices, onions and tomatoes resulting in a rich and flavorful sauce. It\'s a popular dish enjoyed in various cultures worldwide for its comforting and aromatic qualities', '59jznksdk.jpg', '<li>1 kg chicken, cut into pieces</li><li>\r\n2 onions, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2 tomatoes, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n3-4 cloves garlic, minced</li><li>\r\n1-inch piece of ginger, minced</li><li>\r\n2 green chilies, slit lengthwise (adjust to taste)</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon coriander powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon chili powder (adjust to taste)</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon garam masala</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons cooking oil</li><li>\r\nFresh coriander leaves for garnish</li><br/>', 'Heat oil in a large pan or pot over medium heat. Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\r\nAdd chopped onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\r\nAdd minced garlic, ginger, and green chilies. Sauté for a couple of minutes until the raw smell disappears.\r\nAdd chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and mushy.\r\nAdd coriander powder, turmeric powder, chili powder, and salt. Mix well and cook for another 2-3 minutes.\r\nAdd the chicken pieces to the pan and mix them well with the masala. Cook for 5-7 minutes until the chicken starts to brown slightly.\r\nAdd about 1 cup of water, cover the pan, and let it simmer on low heat for about 20-25 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through. Stir occasionally.\r\nOnce the chicken is cooked, sprinkle garam masala and garnish with fresh coriander leaves.\r\nServe hot with rice or naan bread.<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3><br/>\r\nNutrient values are per serving (assuming 4 servings):\r\n<li>\r\nCalories: Approximately 300-350 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: Approximately 25-30 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: Approximately 15-20 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: Approximately 10-15 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: Approximately 2-3 grams</li><li>\r\nSodium: Approximately 500-700 milligrams (varies based on salt added)</li><li>\r\nPotassium: Approximately 400-500 milligrams</li><li>\r\nVitamin C: Approximately 15-20 milligrams</li><li>\r\nIron: Approximately 2-3 milligrams</li>', '52'),
(11, 'Loaded veg pizza\r\n', 'Indulge in a slice of happiness with our irresistible pizzas, crafted with love and topped with flavor. Taste perfection in every bite – your cravings deserve our pizza!', '59hdvhk.jpg', '<li>Pizza dough (store-bought or homemade)</li><li>\r\nTomato sauce or pizza sauce</li><li>\r\nShredded mozzarella cheese</li><li>\r\nAssorted vegetables (bell peppers, onions, mushrooms, olives, tomatoes, spinach, etc.)</li><li>\r\nOlive oil</li><li>\r\nSalt and pepper</li><li>\r\nItalian seasoning (optional)</li><br/>\r\n', 'Preheat your oven to the temperature specified on your pizza dough package or recipe.\r\nRoll out the pizza dough on a floured surface to your desired thickness and shape, then transfer it to a pizza pan or baking sheet.\r\nSpread a layer of tomato sauce or pizza sauce evenly over the pizza dough, leaving a small border around the edges.\r\nSprinkle a generous amount of shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce.\r\nChop your assorted vegetables into bite-sized pieces and arrange them evenly over the cheese.\r\nDrizzle a little olive oil over the vegetables and season with salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning to taste.\r\nBake the pizza in the preheated oven according to the instructions for your pizza dough, usually until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly and melted.\r\nOnce the pizza is done, remove it from the oven and let it cool slightly before slicing and serving<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<br/><li>Calories: Approximately 200-300 calories per slice.</li><li>\r\nProtein: Around 8-12 grams of protein per slice.</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: Roughly 25-35 grams of carbohydrates per slice.</li><li>\r\nFat: Approximately 8-15 grams of fat per slice.</li><li>\r\nFiber: About 2-5 grams of fiber per slice.</li><li>\r\nVitamins and Minerals: The pizza can provide various vitamins and minerals, including vitamin A, vitamin C, calcium, and iron, depending on the vegetables used and their quantities.</li>', '55'),
(12, 'Masala akki roti', 'Savor the spice of tradition with our Masala Akki Roti, a taste of South India in every flavorful bite, crafted with love and heritage.', '6,awkjfh5413.jpg', '<li>1 cup rice flour</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup grated coconut</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup finely chopped onion</li><li>\r\n2-3 green chilies, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons finely chopped coriander leaves</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon grated ginger</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon cumin seeds</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\nWater as needed</li><li>\r\nOil or ghee for cooking</li><br/>\r\n', 'In a mixing bowl, combine the rice flour, grated coconut, chopped onion, green chilies, coriander leaves, grated ginger, turmeric powder, cumin seeds, and salt.\r\nGradually add water to the mixture, little by little, and knead into a soft and pliable dough. The dough should be smooth and not too sticky.\r\nDivide the dough into small portions and shape each portion into a ball.\r\nPlace a ball of dough on a clean, flat surface lined with parchment paper or a banana leaf. Flatten the ball with your fingers to form a thin, round roti.\r\nHeat a tawa or griddle over medium heat and grease it lightly with oil or ghee.\r\nCarefully transfer the flattened roti onto the hot tawa and cook for a few minutes on each side until golden brown spots appear and the roti is cooked through. Drizzle a little oil or ghee around the edges while cooking.\r\nRepeat the process with the remaining dough balls to make more rotis.\r\nServe the masala akki roti hot with a side of coconut chutney, pickle, or yogurt.</br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3></br>\r\n<li>Calories: Around 150-200 calories per roti, depending on the size and thickness.</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: Approximately 25-30 grams of carbohydrates per roti.</li><li>\r\nProtein: Roughly 2-4 grams of protein per roti, primarily from the rice flour and coconut.</li><li>\r\nFat: About 5-8 grams of fat per roti, mostly from the coconut and any added oil or ghee for cooking.</li><li>\r\nFiber: Around 1-2 grams of fiber per roti, provided by the rice flour, onions and green chilies.</li><li>\r\nVitamins and Minerals:Provide various vitamins and minerals, including iron, calcium, and vitamin C from ingredients like onions, coriander leaves, and coconut.</li>', '56'),
(13, ' Chicken Biryani', 'Savor the exquisite taste of tradition with our Chicken Biryani, where tender chicken and fragrant spices come together in perfect harmony. Each bite is a journey of flavor, transporting you to the vibrant streets of India. Experience the ultimate culinary delight with every spoonful of our authentic Chicken Biryani.\"', 'ahwgfsh.jpg', 'For Marinating Chicken:<br/><li>\r\n500 grams chicken, cut into pieces</li><li>\r\n1 cup yogurt</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons ginger-garlic paste</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon lemon juice</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon chili powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><br/>\r\nFor Rice:<br/><li>\r\n2 cups basmati rice, soaked for 30 minutes and drained</li><li>\r\nWater for cooking rice</li><li>\r\n2-3 green cardamom pods</li><li>\r\n2-3 cloves</li><li>\r\n1-inch cinnamon stick</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><br/>\r\nFor Biryani Masala:<br/><li>\r\n2 onions, thinly sliced</li><li>\r\n2 tomatoes, chopped</li><li>\r\n2 green chilies, slit</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup chopped coriander leaves</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup chopped mint leaves</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon chili powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon biryani masala powder</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\nOil or ghee for cooking</li><br/>\r\nFor Layering:<br/><li>\r\nFried onions (optional)</li><li>\r\nSaffron strands soaked in warm milk (optional)</li><li>\r\nGhee for drizzling</li><br/>\r\n\r\n', 'Marinate the chicken: In a bowl, mix together yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, lemon juice, chili powder, turmeric powder, and salt. Add chicken pieces to the marinade, coat them well, cover, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.\r\nCook the rice: In a large pot, bring water to a boil. Add soaked and drained rice along with whole spices (cardamom, cloves, cinnamon), and salt. Cook rice until it is 70-80% done. Drain the rice and set aside.\r\nPrepare the biryani masala: In a separate pan, heat oil or ghee. Add sliced onions and sauté until golden brown. Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until fragrant. Add chopped tomatoes, green chilies, chili powder, turmeric powder, biryani masala powder, coriander leaves, mint leaves, and salt. Cook until the tomatoes are soft and the masala is thickened.\r\nLayering: In a heavy-bottomed pan or pressure cooker, layer half of the cooked rice. Spread the cooked chicken and biryani masala over the rice layer. Top with the remaining rice. Sprinkle fried onions and saffron milk over the rice. Drizzle ghee over the top.\r\nDum Cooking: Cover the pan with a tight-fitting lid or seal with dough. Cook biryani on low heat (dum) for about 20-25 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and the flavors are well absorbed.\r\nOnce done, gently fluff the biryani with a fork. Serve hot with raita or salan (curry).\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3><br/>\r\n<li>Calories: Around 400-500 calories per serving, depending on portion size and ingredients used.</li><li>\r\nProtein: Approximately 20-25 grams of protein per serving, mainly from the chicken.</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: Roughly 40-50 grams of carbohydrates from the rice and vegetables.</li><li>\r\nFat: About 15-20 grams of fat per serving, mostly from the chicken and any added oil or ghee.</li><li>\r\nFiber: Depending on the amount of vegetables used, each serving may provide 2-4 grams of fiber.</li><li>\r\nVitamins and Minerals: Chicken Biryani can be a good source of various vitamins and minerals,          including vitamin C, vitamin A, iron, and calcium, depending on the ingredients used in the recipe.</li>', '58'),
(14, 'Fish curry\r\n', 'Savor the exotic flavors of our fish curry, a culinary journey to coastal bliss. Infused with aromatic spices and tender fish fillets, it\'s a symphony of taste that will leave you craving more. Indulge in a dish that\'s not just a meal, but an experience worth savoring.', '59erus.jpg', '<li>500g fish fillets (such as cod, tilapia, or salmon)</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li><li>\r\n1 onion, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2 garlic cloves, minced</li><li>\r\n1-inch piece of ginger, grated</li><li>\r\n2 tomatoes, chopped</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon curry powder</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon ground cumin</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon ground coriander</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper (adjust to taste)</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\n1 cup coconut milk</li><li>\r\nFresh cilantro for garnish</li><li>\r\nCooked rice or naan bread for serving</li>\r\n', 'Heat the vegetable oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.\r\nAdd the minced garlic and grated ginger to the pan and cook for another 2 minutes until fragrant.\r\nStir in the chopped tomatoes and cook until they start to break down, about 5 minutes.\r\nAdd the curry powder, ground cumin, ground coriander, turmeric powder, cayenne pepper, and salt to the pan. Cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly, until the spices are fragrant.\r\nPour in the coconut milk and bring the mixture to a simmer.\r\nGently place the fish fillets into the curry sauce, making sure they are submerged. Cover the pan and let the fish cook for about 8-10 minutes, or until cooked through and flaky.\r\nOnce the fish is cooked, taste the curry and adjust the seasoning if needed.\r\nGarnish with fresh cilantro and serve hot with rice or naan bread.<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3><br/>\r\n<li>Protein: Fish is an excellent source of high-quality protein, which is essential for muscle growth and repair, as well as overall body function.</li><li>\r\nOmega-3 Fatty Acids: Fish, especially fatty fish like salmon, provides omega-3 fatty acids, which are beneficial for heart health, brain function, and reducing inflammation in the body.</li><li>Vitamins: Fish is rich in vitamins such as vitamin D, which is important for bone health and immune function, and B vitamins like B12 and niacin, which play roles in energy metabolism and nervous system function.</li><li>Minerals: Fish is a good source of minerals such as iodine, which is important for thyroid function, and selenium, which acts as an antioxidant and supports thyroid health and immune function.</li><li>Coconut Milk: Coconut milk adds creaminess to the curry and provides medium-chain triglycerides (MCTs), which are a type of healthy fat that can be easily converted into energy by the body.</li><li>Spices: The spices used in the curry, such as turmeric, cumin, coriander, and garlic, not only add flavor but also provide antioxidants and have anti-inflammatory properties.</li>', '59'),
(15, 'Paneer Tikka Masala', 'Indulge in the rich flavors of Paneer Tikka Masala, a tantalizing symphony of spices and creamy goodness. Savor tender paneer cubes marinated in a vibrant blend of yogurt and aromatic spices, simmered to perfection in a luscious tomato-based sauce. Elevate your dining experience with this iconic dish, a true celebration of Indian culinary excellence.', 'kjrsnfvkj.jpg', '250 grams paneer (Indian cottage cheese), cut into cubes\r\n1 cup yogurt\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste\r\n<li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon red chili powder</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon garam masala</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons oil</li><li>\r\n1 onion, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2 tomatoes, pureed</li><li>\r\n1 green bell pepper, diced</li><li>\r\n1 red bell pepper, diced</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon coriander powder</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon kasuri methi (dried fenugreek leaves)</li><li>\r\nFresh cilantro leaves for garnish</li><br/>\r\n', 'In a bowl, mix together yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt.\r\nAdd paneer cubes to the marinade and coat them well. Let them marinate for at least 30 minutes.\r\nHeat oil in a pan over medium heat. Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.\r\nAdd finely chopped onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.\r\nAdd pureed tomatoes and cook until the oil starts to separate from the masala.\r\nAdd diced bell peppers and cook for a few minutes until they soften slightly.\r\nAdd coriander powder and kasuri methi, and mix well.\r\nNow, add the marinated paneer along with the marinade into the pan. Cook for another 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally.\r\nAdjust the seasoning according to your taste.\r\nGarnish with fresh cilantro leaves.\r\nServe hot with naan or rice.\r\nEnjoy your homemade Paneer Tikka Masala!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li>Calories: 320 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 14g</li><li>\r\nFat: 22g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 8g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 20g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 4g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 10g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 760mg</li><br/>\r\n<b>Note:</b>\r\nPlease note that these values are approximate and can vary based on factors like specific ingredients used and portion sizes.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '10'),
(16, 'Chicken Shawarma Roll', 'Wrap up your cravings with our Chicken Shawarma Roll, a savory sensation bursting with Mediterranean flavors. Tender marinated chicken, crisp vegetables, and creamy tahini sauce all rolled into one delightful bite. It\'s a taste of the Middle East, wrapped and ready for your enjoyment!', 'xghfy.jpg', '<li>500 grams boneless, skinless chicken thighs or breasts, thinly sliced</li><li>\r\n4-6 pita bread or Lebanese flatbreads</li><li>\r\n1 cup plain yogurt</li><li>\r\n3 cloves garlic, minced</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons lemon juice</li><li>\r\n2 teaspoons ground cumin</li><li>\r\n2 teaspoons paprika</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon ground coriander</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon ground turmeric</li><li>\r\nSalt and black pepper to taste</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons olive oil</li><li>\r\nThinly sliced lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers, and onions for serving</li><li>\r\nTahini sauce or garlic sauce for serving (optional)</li>\r\n<br/>\r\n', 'In a bowl, mix together yogurt, minced garlic, lemon juice, ground cumin, paprika, ground coriander, ground turmeric, salt, and black pepper to make the marinade.\r\nAdd the thinly sliced chicken to the marinade and coat well. Let it marinate for at least 30 minutes, or refrigerate for up to 4 hours for more flavor.\r\nHeat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add the marinated chicken and cook until it is fully cooked and slightly browned, about 6-8 minutes.\r\nWarm the pita bread or Lebanese flatbreads in the oven or on a skillet for a few seconds.\r\nTo assemble the shawarma rolls, place a spoonful of cooked chicken onto the center of each bread. Top with sliced lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers, onions, and drizzle with tahini sauce or garlic sauce if desired.\r\nRoll up the bread tightly around the filling, securing it with foil or parchment paper if needed.\r\nServe the chicken shawarma rolls warm and enjoy!\r\n<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3>\r\n<br/><li>Calories: 400 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 25g</li><li>\r\nFat: 15g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 3g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 40g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 3g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 3g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 600mg</li>', '11'),
(17, 'Bisi bele bath \r\n', 'Experience the rich tapestry of South Indian flavors with our Bisi Bele Bath, a symphony of spices and wholesome goodness in every bite. Delight in the aromatic blend of rice, lentils, and vegetables, perfectly seasoned to tantalize your taste buds. A comforting classic that brings warmth to your soul with every spoonful.', '56kjHFs.jpg\r\n', '<li>1 cup rice</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup toor dal (split pigeon peas), washed and soaked for 30 minutes</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup mixed vegetables (carrots, beans, peas, etc.), chopped</li><li>\r\n1 small onion, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2 tomatoes, chopped</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons tamarind pulp</li><li>\r\n3 tablespoons Bisi Bele Bath powder (readily available or homemade)</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons ghee or oil</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon mustard seeds</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li><li>\r\nA pinch of asafoetida (hing)</li><li>\r\nFew curry leaves</li><li>\r\n2-3 dried red chilies</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons roasted peanuts (optional)</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\nChopped coriander leaves for garnish</li><br/>\r\n', 'In a pressure cooker, add rice, soaked toor dal, mixed vegetables, chopped onions, tomatoes, tamarind pulp, Bisi Bele Bath powder, and salt. Add about 4 cups of water and mix well.\r\nPressure cook for 3-4 whistles or until the rice and dal are cooked thoroughly. Alternatively, you can cook it in a pot until the rice and dal are soft and well-cooked.\r\nOnce the pressure releases, mash the mixture slightly with the back of a ladle. Adjust the consistency by adding more water if needed.\r\nHeat ghee or oil in a pan. Add mustard seeds and let them splutter. Then add cumin seeds, asafoetida, dried red chilies, curry leaves, and roasted peanuts. Fry for a minute.\r\nPour this tempering over the cooked Bisi Bele Bath mixture and mix well.\r\nGarnish with chopped coriander leaves.\r\nServe hot with a dollop of ghee on top, along with some papad or potato chips.\r\nEnjoy your flavorful Bisi Bele Bath!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li>Calories: 350 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 12g</li><li>\r\nFat: 7g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 2g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 62g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 9g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 6g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 650mg</li>', '12'),
(18, 'Lotus Biscoff Cheesecake', 'Indulge in divine decadence with our Lotus Biscoff Cheesecake, A heavenly fusion of creamy bliss and irresistible crunch. Elevate your dessert experience with every luscious bite. It\'s the ultimate temptation for Biscoff lovers everywhere!', 'hjgkd.jpg', 'For the crust:\r\n<li>\r\n200g Lotus Biscoff cookies (about 20 cookies)</li><li>\r\n6 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted</li><br/>\r\nFor the cheesecake filling:\r\n<li>\r\n500g cream cheese, softened</li><li>\r\n1 cup Lotus Biscoff spread</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup granulated sugar</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li><li>\r\n1 cup heavy cream</li><br/>\r\nFor the topping:\r\n<li>\r\nLotus Biscoff cookies, crushed</li><li>\r\nLotus Biscoff spread, for drizzling</li><br/>\r\n', '<b>Prepare the crust:</b>\r\nCrush the Lotus Biscoff cookies into fine crumbs using a food processor or by placing them in a zip-top bag and crushing them with a rolling pin.\r\nIn a mixing bowl, combine the cookie crumbs with melted butter until well combined. Press the mixture into the bottom of a 9-inch springform pan. Use the back of a spoon or a flat-bottomed glass to press the crumbs evenly across the bottom of the pan. Chill the crust in the refrigerator while you prepare the filling.<br/>\r\n<b>Prepare the cheesecake filling:</b>\r\nIn a large mixing bowl, beat the softened cream cheese until smooth and creamy.Add the Lotus Biscoff spread, granulated sugar, and vanilla extract. Beat until well combined and smooth.\r\nIn a separate bowl, whip the heavy cream until stiff peaks form.\r\nGently fold the whipped cream into the cream cheese mixture until smooth and well combined.<br/>\r\n<b>Assemble the cheesecake:</b>\r\nPour the cheesecake filling over the chilled crust in the springform pan.\r\nSmooth the top with a spatula.Cover and refrigerate the cheesecake for at least 4 hours or overnight to set.<br/>\r\n<b>Serve:</b>\r\nBefore serving, carefully release the springform pan and transfer the cheesecake to a serving platter.\r\nSprinkle crushed Lotus Biscoff cookies over the top of the cheesecake.\r\nDrizzle additional Lotus Biscoff spread over the cheesecake for extra flavor, if desired.\r\nSlice and serve chilled.\r\nEnjoy your decadent Lotus Biscoff Cheesecake!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 480 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 6g</li><li>\r\nFat: 38g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 21g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 1g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 33g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 1g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 23g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 270mg</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '13'),
(19, 'Carrot Halwa', 'Indulge in the rich heritage of Indian sweets with our Carrot Halwa, a timeless delicacy brimming with warmth and flavor. Experience the blissful marriage of grated carrots, aromatic spices, and creamy milk, crafted to perfection in every spoonful. Savor the sweetness of tradition with each decadent bite.', 'jhvhkluo.jpg', '<li>1 lb (about 450g) carrots, grated</li><li>\r\n4 cups whole milk</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup sugar (adjust to taste)</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup ghee (clarified butter)</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup chopped nuts (almonds, cashews, pistachios)</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon cardamom powder</li><li>\r\nSaffron strands (optional)</li><li>\r\nRaisins for garnish (optional)</li><br/>\r\n', 'Heat ghee in a heavy-bottomed pan or kadai over medium heat.\r\nAdd the grated carrots to the pan and sauté them in the ghee for about 5-7 minutes until they soften and turn aromatic.\r\nPour in the milk and stir well. Allow the mixture to come to a boil.\r\nReduce the heat to low and let the carrots cook in the milk, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking to the bottom of the pan.\r\nCook the carrots until most of the milk evaporates and the mixture thickens. This can take around 30-40 minutes.\r\nOnce the carrots are cooked and the mixture has thickened, add sugar and mix well. Cook for another 5-10 minutes until the sugar is completely dissolved and the halwa reaches a desired consistency.\r\nAdd cardamom powder and mix well. If using saffron strands, you can soak them in a tablespoon of warm milk and add them at this stage for extra flavor and color.In a separate pan, heat a teaspoon of ghee and roast the chopped nuts until golden brown. Add them to the carrot halwa and mix well.\r\nGarnish with raisins if desired.\r\nServe warm or cold, as per your preference.\r\nEnjoy your delicious homemade Carrot Halwa!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 300 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 5g</li><li>\r\nFat: 15g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 8g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 40g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 3g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 35g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 100mg</li>', '14'),
(20, 'Chicken Sandwich', 'Satisfy your cravings with our irresistible Chicken Sandwich,Juicy grilled chicken, fresh veggies, and creamy spreads, all nestled between two slices of toasted perfection. Bite into flavor, bite into satisfaction – it\'s the ultimate sandwich experience!', 'bdskjfvnc.jpg', '<li>2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts\r\nSalt and black pepper to taste</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon olive oil</li><li>\r\n4 slices of bread (your choice of bread, such as whole wheat, ciabatta, or sourdough)</li><li>\r\nLettuce leaves</li><li>\r\nSliced tomatoes</li><li>\r\nSliced red onions (optional)</li><li>\r\nMayonnaise or your favorite sandwich spread</li><li>\r\nMustard (optional)</li><br/>\r\n', 'Season the chicken breasts with salt and black pepper on both sides.\r\nHeat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\r\nAdd the seasoned chicken breasts to the skillet and cook for about 6-8 minutes per side, or until they are cooked through and golden brown on the outside. Ensure the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).\r\nOnce cooked, remove the chicken breasts from the skillet and let them rest for a few minutes. Then slice them into thin strips.\r\nToast the slices of bread until golden brown and crispy.\r\nAssemble the sandwiches by spreading mayonnaise (or your preferred spread) on one side of each slice of bread.\r\nLayer the lettuce leaves, sliced tomatoes, and sliced red onions (if using) on one slice of bread.\r\nPlace the sliced chicken breasts on top of the vegetables.\r\nIf desired, add mustard on top of the chicken.\r\nTop with the remaining slice of bread to form a sandwich.\r\nRepeat the process for the remaining ingredients to make additional sandwiches.\r\nSlice the sandwiches diagonally and serve immediately.\r\nEnjoy your delicious and satisfying Chicken Sandwich!\r\n<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li>Calories: 350 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 25g</li><li>\r\nFat: 12g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 2g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 30g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 4g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 4g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 600mg</li>', '15'),
(21, 'Chocolate Ice Cream', 'A rich symphony of creamy cocoa goodness that delights the senses. Savor the velvety texture and intense flavor, crafted to satisfy your deepest cravings. It\'s a luxurious treat that promises to transport you to chocolate paradise with every spoonful.', 'athzg.sf.jpg', '<li>2 cups heavy cream</li><li>\r\n1 cup whole milk</li><li>\r\n3/4 cup granulated sugar</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder</li><li>\r\n4 ounces semisweet chocolate, chopped</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li><li>\r\nPinch of salt</li><br/>\r\n', 'In a medium saucepan, combine the heavy cream, whole milk, granulated sugar, and unsweetened cocoa powder.\r\nPlace the saucepan over medium heat and whisk continuously until the mixture is smooth and starts to steam. Do not let it boil.\r\nRemove the saucepan from the heat and add the chopped semisweet chocolate. Stir until the chocolate is completely melted and the mixture is smooth.\r\nStir in the vanilla extract and a pinch of salt.\r\nTransfer the mixture to a bowl and let it cool to room temperature.\r\nOnce cooled, cover the bowl and refrigerate the mixture for at least 4 hours or overnight until thoroughly chilled.\r\nOnce chilled, pour the mixture into an ice cream maker and churn according to the manufacturer\'s instructions until it reaches a soft-serve consistency.\r\nTransfer the churned ice cream to a freezer-safe container, cover, and freeze for at least 4 hours or until firm.\r\nBefore serving, let the ice cream sit at room temperature for a few minutes to soften slightly.\r\nScoop the chocolate ice cream into bowls or cones and enjoy!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3><br/>\r\n<li>Calories: 300 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 4g</li><li>\r\nFat: 22g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 14g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 26g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 3g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 20g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 50mg</li>', '16'),
(22, 'Pesto Pasta', 'Embrace the taste of Italy with our vibrant Pesto Pasta, A symphony of fresh basil, garlic, and Parmesan cheese, harmonizing in every bite. Elevate your dining experience with this flavorful classic, crafted to delight your palate with each twirl of pasta. Indulge in a taste of Mediterranean bliss, right in the comfort of your own home.', 'aerlibgj.jpg', '<li>8 ounces (225g) pasta of your choice (such as spaghetti, fettuccine, or penne)</li><li>\r\n2 cups fresh basil leaves, packed</li><li>\r\n2 cloves garlic</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup pine nuts or walnuts</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese</li><li>\r\n1/3 cup extra virgin olive oil</li><li>\r\nSalt and pepper to taste</li><li>\r\nOptional toppings: cherry tomatoes, grated Parmesan cheese, toasted pine nuts, fresh basil leaves</li><br/>\r\n', 'Cook the pasta according to the package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside, reserving a cup of pasta water.\r\nIn a food processor, combine the basil leaves, garlic, pine nuts or walnuts, and grated Parmesan cheese. Pulse until finely chopped.\r\nWith the food processor running, gradually add the olive oil in a steady stream until the mixture forms a smooth paste.\r\nSeason the pesto with salt and pepper to taste. You can also adjust the consistency by adding a little pasta water if needed.\r\nIn a large mixing bowl, toss the cooked pasta with the pesto sauce until well coated.\r\nServe the pesto pasta hot or cold, garnished with optional toppings such as cherry tomatoes, grated Parmesan cheese, toasted pine nuts, or fresh basil leaves.\r\nEnjoy your delicious homemade Pesto Pasta!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 400 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 12g</li><li>\r\nFat: 25g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 4g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 35g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 3g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 1g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 300mg</li>', '17'),
(23, 'French fries', 'Crispy on the outside, fluffy on the inside, and irresistible every time. Indulge in the classic comfort of hand-cut potatoes, fried to perfection and seasoned with just the right amount of salt. Elevate your snacking experience with our timeless favorite, a delicious side that\'s simply impossible to resist.', 'iuadesf.jpg', '<li>4 large russet potatoes</li><li>\r\nVegetable oil, for frying</li><li>\r\nSalt, to taste</li>\r\n<br/>', 'Peel the potatoes and cut them into even-sized sticks, about 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.\r\nRinse the potato sticks under cold water to remove excess starch. Then, pat them dry thoroughly with paper towels.\r\nHeat vegetable oil in a deep fryer or large pot to 325°F (160°C).\r\nWorking in batches, carefully add the potato sticks to the hot oil, making sure not to overcrowd the fryer/pot. Fry for about 3-4 minutes, until they are pale golden and partially cooked.\r\nRemove the partially cooked fries from the oil using a slotted spoon or wire skimmer, and transfer them to a paper towel-lined tray to drain excess oil.\r\nIncrease the temperature of the oil to 375°F (190°C).\r\nOnce the oil reaches the desired temperature, carefully add the partially cooked fries back into the hot oil in batches. Fry for an additional 2-3 minutes, or until they are golden brown and crispy.\r\nRemove the fries from the oil and transfer them to a paper towel-lined tray to drain any excess oil.\r\nImmediately season the hot fries with salt, to taste.\r\nServe the French fries hot and crispy with your favorite dipping sauce.\r\nEnjoy your homemade French fries!\r\n<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 300 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 3g</li><li>\r\nFat: 14g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 1g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 41g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 4g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 2g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 400mg</li>', '18'),
(24, 'Eggless Brownies', 'Rich, fudgy, and utterly delightful with every bite. Experience the perfect balance of moist texture and intense chocolate flavor, crafted to satisfy your sweet cravings. It\'s the ultimate treat for chocolate lovers everywhere.', 'djhgckjb.jpg', '<li>1 cup all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon baking soda</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon salt</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted</li><li>\r\n1 cup granulated sugar</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup milk (dairy or non-dairy)</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup chocolate chips or chopped</li><li> chocolate (optional)</li><br/>\r\n', 'Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease or line an 8x8-inch baking pan with parchment paper and set aside.\r\nIn a mixing bowl, sift together the all-purpose flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Mix well to combine.\r\nIn a separate large mixing bowl, whisk together the melted butter and granulated sugar until smooth.\r\nAdd the milk and vanilla extract to the butter-sugar mixture and whisk until well combined.\r\nGradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, stirring until just combined. Be careful not to overmix.\r\nFold in the chocolate chips or chopped chocolate, if using.\r\nPour the brownie batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly with a spatula.\r\nBake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter).\r\nRemove the brownies from the oven and allow them to cool completely in the pan before slicing and serving.\r\nEnjoy your delicious homemade Eggless Brownies!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values </h3><br/>\r\n<li>Calories: 250 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 3g</li><li>\r\nFat: 12g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 7g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 35g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 2g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 20g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 150mg</li>', '19'),
(25, 'Samosas', 'Experience the exquisite blend of spices and textures in every bite of our samosas: Crispy on the outside, flavorful on the inside, and utterly satisfying till the last crumb. Indulge in a culinary journey that captures the essence of Indian street food, bringing joy to your taste buds with each delicious triangle.\"', '59hud21.jpg', 'For the dough:<br/><li>\r\n2 cups all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup vegetable oil or melted ghee</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon salt</li><li>\r\nWater, as needed</li><br/>\r\nFor the filling:<br/><li>\r\n2 medium potatoes, boiled, peeled, and mashed</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup green peas, boiled (fresh or frozen)</li><li>\r\n1 small onion, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2 green chilies, finely chopped (adjust to taste)</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon coriander powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon garam masala</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon lemon juice</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro leaves</li><li>\r\nVegetable oil for deep frying</li><br/>\r\n', '<b>Prepare the dough:</b>\r\nIn a large mixing bowl, combine the all-purpose flour, salt, and vegetable oil or melted ghee.Gradually add water and knead until you have a smooth, firm dough. Cover the dough and let it rest for 30 minutes.<br/>\r\n<b>Prepare the filling:</b>\r\nHeat a tablespoon of oil in a pan over medium heat. Add the cumin seeds and let them splutter.\r\nAdd the chopped onions and green chilies, and sauté until the onions turn translucent.\r\nAdd the ginger-garlic paste and sauté for another minute.\r\nAdd the boiled and mashed potatoes, boiled green peas, coriander powder, turmeric powder, garam masala, lemon juice, salt, and chopped cilantro leaves. Mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes. Remove from heat and let the filling cool.<br/>\r\n<b>Assemble the samosas:</b>\r\nDivide the dough into equal-sized balls and roll each ball into a thin circle (about 6 inches in diameter). Cut each circle in half to form two semi-circles.\r\nTake one semi-circle and fold it into a cone shape, overlapping the edges slightly. Seal the edges by pressing them together.\r\nFill the cone with a tablespoon of the prepared filling. Seal the open end of the cone by pressing the edges together firmly.\r\nRepeat the process with the remaining dough and filling to make all the samosas.<br/>\r\n<b>Deep fry the samosas:</b>\r\nHeat vegetable oil in a deep frying pan or kadai over medium heat.\r\nOnce the oil is hot, carefully slide in the prepared samosas in batches, without overcrowding the pan.\r\nFry the samosas until they turn golden brown and crispy on all sides, turning occasionally. This should take about 6-8 minutes per batch.\r\nRemove the fried samosas from the oil using a slotted spoon and drain them on paper towels to remove excess oil.\r\nServe the samosas hot with green chutney, tamarind chutney, or ketchup.\r\nEnjoy your delicious homemade Samosas!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3><br/>\r\n<li>Calories: 150 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 3g</li><li>\r\nFat: 8g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 1g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 17g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 2g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 1g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 150mg</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '20'),
(26, 'Paneer Tandoori Momos', 'Experience the tantalizing fusion of flavors with our Paneer Tandoori Momos: A delectable marriage of succulent paneer and aromatic spices, wrapped in a crispy shell. Elevate your snacking game with these irresistible bites, perfect for any occasion. Delight in the taste of tradition reinvented, crafted to tantalize your taste buds with every savory bite.\"', 'knzsf.jpg', 'For the filling:<li>\r\n200g paneer (Indian cottage cheese), crumbled</li><li>\r\n1 onion, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n1 capsicum (bell pepper), finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2-3 green chilies, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon garam masala</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon chaat masala</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\nFresh coriander leaves, chopped</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon oil</li><br/>\r\nFor the momo wrappers:<li>\r\n1 cup all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\nWater, as needed</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><br/>\r\nFor the tandoori marinade:<li>\r\n1/4 cup yogurt</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon tandoori masala powder</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon lemon juice</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon oil</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><br/>\r\n', '<b>Prepare the filling:</b>\r\nHeat oil in a pan over medium heat. Add chopped onions and sauté until translucent.\r\nAdd ginger-garlic paste and chopped green chilies. Sauté for another minute.\r\nAdd chopped capsicum and cook for a few minutes until slightly softened.\r\nAdd crumbled paneer, garam masala, chaat masala, salt, and chopped coriander leaves. Mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes. Remove from heat and let the filling cool.<br/>\r\n<b>Prepare the momo wrappers:</b>\r\nIn a mixing bowl, combine all-purpose flour and salt. Gradually add water and knead until you have a smooth dough. Cover the dough and let it rest for 30 minutes.\r\nAfter resting, divide the dough into small balls. Roll each ball into a thin circle, about 3-4 inches in diameter.<br/>\r\n<b>Assemble the momos:</b>\r\nPlace a spoonful of the prepared paneer filling in the center of each rolled-out dough circle.\r\nFold the edges of the dough circle over the filling to form a half-moon shape. Pinch and pleat the edges together to seal the momo.\r\nPrepare the tandoori marinade:\r\nIn a bowl, mix yogurt, tandoori masala powder, lemon juice, oil, and salt to taste. Stir until well combined.<br/>\r\n<b>Marinate the momos:</b>\r\nDip each sealed momo in the tandoori marinade, ensuring it is well coated. Place the marinated momos in a shallow dish and let them marinate for at least 30 minutes.<br/>\r\n<b>Cook the momos:</b>\r\nPreheat the oven to 180°C (350°F). Place the marinated momos on a baking tray lined with parchment paper.\r\nBake in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes or until the momos are cooked through and the marinade is slightly charred.\r\nServe hot with mint chutney or any dipping sauce of your choice.\r\nEnjoy your delicious Paneer Tandoori Momos!<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<br/><li>\r\nCalories: 250 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 12g</li><li>\r\nFat: 8g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 3g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 35g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 3g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 3g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 500mg</li>\r\n\r\n', '21'),
(27, 'Avocado Milkshake', 'Savor the creamy indulgence of our Avocado Milkshake, A luscious blend of ripe avocado and cold milk, creating a silky-smooth sensation with every sip. Elevate your refreshment game with this nutritious treat, packed with essential nutrients and delightful flavor. It\'s the perfect fusion of health and indulgence, crafted to tantalize your taste buds and nourish your body.', '561564.jpg', '<li>1 ripe avocado</li><li>\r\n1 cup cold milk (dairy or non-dairy)</li><li>\r\n2-3 tablespoons sweetened condensed milk or honey (adjust to taste)</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional)</li><li>\r\nIce cubes (optional)</li><br/>\r\n', 'Cut the ripe avocado in half, remove the pit, and scoop out the flesh into a blender.\r\nAdd cold milk, sweetened condensed milk or honey, and vanilla extract to the blender.\r\nBlend all the ingredients together until smooth and creamy. If desired, you can add a few ice cubes to make the milkshake colder and thicker.\r\nTaste the milkshake and adjust the sweetness according to your preference by adding more sweetened condensed milk or honey if needed.\r\nOnce you achieve the desired consistency and sweetness, pour the avocado milkshake into glasses.\r\nServe immediately and enjoy your creamy and refreshing Avocado Milkshake!\r\nFeel free to customize your milkshake by adding a splash of lime juice, a scoop of vanilla ice cream, or a handful of spinach for extra nutrients.<br/>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3><br/>\r\n<li>Calories: 250 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 5g</li><li>\r\nFat: 15g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 3g</li><li>\r\nTrans Fat: 0g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 25g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 7g</li><li>\r\nSugars: 15g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 100mg</li>\r\n', '22'),
(28, 'Masala Dosa', 'Delight in every bite with our crispy, golden masala dosa, bursting with a symphony of flavorful spices and savory potato filling. Indulge in a South Indian classic that\'s both comforting and exotic, perfect for any time of day', 'khABLv.jpg', '<li>1 cup rice (preferably parboiled or idli rice)</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup urad dal (split black lentils)</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup chana dal (split chickpeas)</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup poha (flattened rice)</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\n1 tsp fenugreek seeds</li><li>\r\nOil or ghee for cooking</li><br>\r\n<b>\r\nFor the potato filling (Masala):</b>\r\n<li>\r\n3 medium potatoes, boiled and mashed</li><li>\r\n1 onion, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n2 green chilies, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n1/2 tsp mustard seeds</li><li>\r\n1/2 tsp cumin seeds</li><li>\r\nA pinch of asafoetida (hing)</li><li>\r\nFew curry leaves</li><li>\r\n1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\n1 tbsp oil</li><br>', '<b>For Dosa Batter:</b>\r\n\r\nRinse and soak rice, urad dal, chana dal, and fenugreek seeds together for about 6-8 hours.\r\nRinse poha and add it to the soaked ingredients.\r\nGrind everything together to a smooth batter consistency. Add water as needed. The batter should be slightly thick.\r\nFerment the batter overnight or for at least 8-10 hours in a warm place.<br>\r\n<b>Potato Filling (Masala):</b>\r\n\r\nHeat oil in a pan, add mustard seeds and let them splutter.\r\nAdd cumin seeds, asafoetida, and curry leaves. Saute for a few seconds.\r\nAdd chopped onions and green chilies. Saute until onions turn translucent.\r\nAdd turmeric powder and mix well.\r\nAdd mashed potatoes and salt. Mix until well combined. Cook for 2-3 minutes. Masala is ready.<br>\r\n<b>Making Dosas:</b>\r\n\r\nHeat a dosa tawa (griddle) and grease it lightly with oil or ghee.\r\nPour a ladleful of batter onto the tawa and spread it evenly in a circular motion to form a thin layer.\r\nDrizzle some oil or ghee around the edges of the dosa.\r\nOnce the bottom turns golden brown and crispy, place a portion of the potato filling (masala) on one half of the dosa.\r\nFold the dosa over the filling to form a semi-circle or roll it up.\r\nServe hot with coconut chutney and sambar.<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 250-300 kcal</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 50-60 g</li><li>\r\nProtein: 5-7 g</li><li>\r\nFat: 2-4 g</li><li>\r\nFiber: 3-5 g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 400-500 mg</li><li>\r\nVitamin C: 10-15 mg</li><li>\r\nIron: 1-2 mg</li>\r\n', '28'),
(29, 'Millet Dosa', 'Elevate your mornings with our Millet Dosa. A nutritious twist on a classic favorite. Packed with wholesome millet goodness, it\'s a gluten-free delight that energizes and satisfies. Start your day right with the perfect blend of health and flavor.', 'ifjvn.jpg', '<li>1 cup millet flour (you can use any millet flour like ragi, bajra, or jowar)</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup rice flour</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup urad dal (split black gram)</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\nWater as needed</li><li>\r\nOil or ghee for cooking</li><br>\r\n', 'Soak the urad dal in water for 4-6 hours or overnight.\r\nRinse and drain the urad dal, then grind it with a little water to make a smooth batter. The batter should be thick and fluffy.\r\nIn a large bowl, mix together the millet flour, rice flour, and salt.\r\nGradually add the urad dal batter to the flour mixture, stirring continuously to combine.\r\nAdd water as needed to make a smooth and pourable batter, similar to the consistency of regular dosa batter.\r\nHeat a non-stick dosa tawa or skillet over medium heat. Once hot, pour a ladleful of the batter onto the tawa and spread it out in a circular motion to form a thin dosa.\r\nDrizzle a little oil or ghee around the edges of the dosa and cook until the bottom is golden brown and crisp.\r\nFlip the dosa and cook the other side until golden brown.\r\nRemove the dosa from the tawa and serve hot with chutney, sambar, or any side dish of your choice.\r\nEnjoy your nutritious and delicious millet dosa!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 120-150 kcal</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 20-25 grams</li><li>\r\nProtein: 3-5 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: 3-5 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: 2-3 grams</li>\r\n', '29'),
(30, 'Oats Smoothie', 'Start your day with a sip of vitality. Oats Smoothie - the perfect blend of nourishment and flavor. Fuel your body with wholesome goodness in every creamy, delicious gulp. Elevate your mornings with the ultimate power-packed breakfast companion.', 'jiadvn.jpg', '<li>1/2 cup rolled oats</li><li>\r\n1 ripe banana</li><li>\r\n1 cup milk (dairy or plant-based)</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup yogurt (optional)</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup (optional)</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional)</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup fresh or frozen fruit of your choice (such as berries, mango, or pineapple)</li><li>\r\nIce cubes (optional)</li><br>\r\n', 'In a blender, add the rolled oats and blend until they form a fine powder.\r\nAdd the banana, milk, yogurt, honey or maple syrup, and vanilla extract to the blender.\r\nAdd the fresh or frozen fruit of your choice.\r\nIf desired, add a few ice cubes for a colder smoothie.\r\nBlend all the ingredients until smooth and creamy.\r\nTaste the smoothie and adjust the sweetness or consistency if needed by adding more honey, milk, or fruit.\r\nPour the smoothie into glasses and serve immediately.\r\nEnjoy your delicious and nutritious oats smoothie! Feel free to customize it with your favorite fruits and toppings.<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient value</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 250-300 kcal</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 40-50 grams</li><li>\r\nProtein: 8-10 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: 5-7 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: 5-7 grams</li>\r\n\r\n', '30');
