(31, 'Chickpea Salad', 'Elevate your plate with our vibrant Chickpea Salad: a burst of flavor and nutrition in every bite. Packed with protein, fiber, and essential nutrients, it\'s a refreshing choice for any meal. Experience the perfect harmony of taste and health with every forkful.', 'lkzjsnfb.jpg', '<li>1 can (15 ounces) chickpeas (garbanzo beans), drained and rinsed</li><li>\r\n1 cucumber, diced</li><li>\r\n1 bell pepper, diced (any color you prefer)</li><li>\r\n1 small red onion, finely chopped</li><li>\r\n1 tomato, diced</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro or parsley</li><li>\r\nJuice of 1 lemon</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil</li><li>\r\nSalt and pepper to taste</li><li>\r\nOptional: crumbled feta cheese, olives, avocado slices, or any other toppings of your choice</li><br>\r\n', 'In a large bowl, combine the chickpeas, cucumber, bell pepper, red onion, tomato, and chopped cilantro or parsley.\r\nIn a small bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, olive oil, salt, and pepper to make the dressing.\r\nPour the dressing over the salad and toss gently to coat all the ingredients.\r\nTaste the salad and adjust the seasoning if needed.\r\nIf desired, add any optional toppings such as crumbled feta cheese, olives, or avocado slices.\r\nServe the chickpea salad immediately, or refrigerate it for a couple of hours to allow the flavors to meld together before serving.\r\nEnjoy your refreshing and nutritious chickpea salad! It\'s perfect as a side dish or a light meal on its own.<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient value</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 250-300 kcal</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 30-35 grams</li><li>\r\nProtein: 8-10 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: 10-12 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: 8-10 grams</li>\r\n\r\n', '31'),
(32, 'Paneer Sandwich', 'Indulge in a burst of Indian flavors with our tantalizing Paneer Sandwich - a fusion of vibrant veggies, aromatic spices, and creamy paneer, nestled between perfectly toasted bread slices. Elevate your sandwich game with this savory delight, a true taste sensation for every palate!', 'hfbv.jpg', '<li>200 grams paneer (Indian cottage cheese), grated or sliced</li><li>\r\n8 slices of bread (white, wheat, or multigrain)</li><li>\r\n1 medium onion, thinly sliced</li><li>\r\n1 medium tomato, thinly sliced</li><li>\r\n1 small capsicum (bell pepper), thinly sliced</li><li>\r\n2 green chilies, finely chopped (optional)</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon cumin powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon coriander powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon garam masala</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li><li>\r\nButter or ghee for toasting</li><li>\r\nMint chutney or ketchup for serving (optional)</li><br>', 'Heat some oil in a pan over medium heat. Add the ginger-garlic paste and sauté until fragrant.\r\nAdd the sliced onions and green chilies (if using) to the pan. Sauté until the onions turn translucent.\r\nAdd the sliced capsicum and tomato to the pan. Cook for a few minutes until the vegetables are slightly softened.\r\nAdd the turmeric powder, cumin powder, coriander powder, garam masala, and salt to the pan. Mix well and cook for another minute.\r\nAdd the grated or sliced paneer to the pan. Mix gently until the paneer is coated with the spices and vegetables. Cook for 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Turn off the heat and let the mixture cool slightly.\r\nTake a slice of bread and place a generous amount of the paneer mixture on it. Cover with another slice of bread to make a sandwich.\r\nHeat a griddle or a pan over medium heat. Spread some butter or ghee on both sides of the sandwich.\r\nPlace the sandwich on the griddle or pan and toast until golden brown on both sides, flipping halfway through. Press gently with a spatula while toasting to ensure the sandwich cooks evenly and the paneer mixture inside gets warm and gooey.\r\nOnce the sandwich is toasted to your liking, remove it from the pan and place it on a plate.\r\nCut the sandwich diagonally into halves or quarters.\r\nServe hot with mint chutney or ketchup on the side, if desired. Enjoy your delicious paneer sandwich!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: Around 300-350 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: Approximately 15-20 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: About 30-35 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: Around 15-20 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: Roughly 3-5 grams</li><li>\r\nSodium: Varies depending on salt added, typically around 500-700 mg</li><li>\r\nCalcium: Approximately 150-200 mg</li><li>\r\nIron: Around 2-3 mg</li><li>\r\nVitamin C: Varies based on the amount of vegetables used, typically 10-20 mg</li>\r\n\r\n', '32'),
(33, 'Chocochip cookies', 'Indulge in the timeless delight of homemade chocolate chip cookies, crafted with love and care. Crispy on the edges, soft and chewy in the center, these cookies are a comforting treat for any occasion, perfect for satisfying your sweet cravings.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'awlifsn.jpg', '<li>1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, softened</li><li>\r\n3/4 cup granulated sugar</li><li>\r\n3/4 cup packed brown sugar</li><li>\r\n2 large eggs</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li><li>\r\n2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon baking soda</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon salt</li><li>\r\n2 cups semisweet chocolate chips</li><br>', 'Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C). Line baking sheets with parchment paper or lightly grease them.\r\n\r\nIn a large mixing bowl, cream together the softened butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar until light and fluffy.\r\n\r\nAdd the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract.\r\n\r\nIn a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, and salt.\r\n\r\nGradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. Be careful not to overmix.\r\n\r\nFold in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed throughout the dough.\r\n\r\nDrop rounded tablespoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheets, spacing them about 2 inches apart.\r\n\r\nBake in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the cookies are golden brown around the edges.\r\n\r\nAllow the cookies to cool on the baking sheets for a few minutes before transferring them to wire racks to cool completely.\r\n\r\nOnce cooled, store the cookies in an airtight container at room temperature for up to a week.\r\n\r\nEnjoy your delicious homemade chocolate chip cookies with a glass of milk or your favorite hot beverage!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: Around 150-200 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: Approximately 2-3 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: About 20-25 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: Around 8-10 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: Roughly 1 gram</li><li>\r\nSodium: Varies depending on salt added, typically around 100-150 mg</li><li>\r\nSugar: Around 10-15 grams</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '33'),
(34, 'Butter biscuits', 'Delight in the comforting simplicity of homemade butter biscuits, golden and flaky with a buttery crumb. Whether enjoyed warm from the oven or paired with your favorite spread, these biscuits bring warmth and nostalgia to every bite.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'wasizfnk.jpg', '<li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\n1 tablespoon baking powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon salt</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup unsalted butter, cold and cubed</li><li>\r\n3/4 cup milk (plus more for brushing)</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons granulated sugar (optional, for sweeter biscuits)</li><br>', 'Preheat your oven to 425°F (220°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or lightly grease it.\r\n\r\nIn a large mixing bowl, whisk together the all-purpose flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar (if using).\r\n\r\nAdd the cold, cubed butter to the dry ingredients. Use a pastry cutter or your fingers to cut the butter into the flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs. You can also use a food processor for this step, pulsing until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.\r\n\r\nMake a well in the center of the mixture and pour in the milk. Stir gently with a wooden spoon or spatula until the dough just comes together. Be careful not to overmix.\r\n\r\nTurn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Pat the dough into a rectangle about 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick.\r\n\r\nUse a biscuit cutter or a drinking glass to cut out biscuits from the dough. Press straight down without twisting the cutter to ensure the biscuits rise properly. Gather any remaining dough, pat it out again, and continue cutting until all the dough is used.\r\n\r\nPlace the biscuits onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.\r\n\r\nLightly brush the tops of the biscuits with milk to help them brown in the oven.\r\n\r\nBake in the preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until the biscuits are golden brown on top and cooked through.\r\n\r\nOnce baked, remove the biscuits from the oven and transfer them to a wire rack to cool slightly before serving.\r\n\r\nEnjoy your delicious homemade butter biscuits with butter, jam, honey, or your favorite spread!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: Around 150-200 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: Approximately 2-3 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: About 15-20 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: Around 8-10 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: Roughly 1 gram</li><li>\r\nSodium: Varies depending on salt added, typically around 200-300 mg</li><li>\r\nSugar: Approximately 1-2 grams</li><br>\r\n<b>Note</b>\r\nPlease note that these values are estimates and can vary based on specific ingredients and portion sizes used.', '34'),
(35, 'Ragi biscuits', 'Savor the wholesome goodness of homemade ragi biscuits - a delightful blend of nutritious finger millet flour and aromatic spices. Baked to perfection, these golden treats offer a guilt-free indulgence for any time of day, bursting with flavor and goodness in every bite.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'fsjc.jpg', '<li>1 cup ragi flour (finger millet flour)</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup whole wheat flour</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup powdered sugar (adjust to taste)</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup unsalted butter, softened</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup milk (adjust as needed)</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon baking powder</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon cardamom powder (optional)</li><li>\r\nPinch of salt</li><br>\r\n', 'Preheat your oven to 350°F (180°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or lightly grease it.\r\n\r\nIn a mixing bowl, combine the ragi flour, whole wheat flour, powdered sugar, baking powder, cardamom powder (if using), and a pinch of salt.\r\n\r\nAdd the softened butter to the dry ingredients. Use your fingers or a fork to mix the butter into the flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.\r\n\r\nGradually add the milk, a little at a time, and knead the mixture into a smooth dough. Be careful not to add too much milk; the dough should hold together without being too sticky.\r\n\r\nRoll out the dough on a lightly floured surface to about 1/4 inch thickness. Use cookie cutters to cut out shapes or simply slice the dough into squares or rectangles.\r\n\r\nPlace the biscuits on the prepared baking sheet, leaving a little space between each biscuit.\r\n\r\nBake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the biscuits are firm to the touch and lightly golden brown around the edges.\r\n\r\nOnce baked, remove the biscuits from the oven and let them cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes.\r\n\r\nTransfer the biscuits to a wire rack to cool completely.\r\n\r\nOnce cooled, store the ragi biscuits in an airtight container at room temperature. Enjoy them as a healthy snack or with your favorite hot beverage!\r\n\r\nFeel free to adjust the sweetness and flavorings according to your preference. Enjoy your homemade ragi biscuits!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: Around 50-60 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: Approximately 1-2 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: About 6-8 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: Around 2-3 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: Roughly 1 gram</li><li>\r\nSodium: Varies depending on salt added, typically minimal</li><li>\r\nSugar: Approximately 2-3 grams</li><br>\r\n<b>Note</b>\r\nPlease note that these values are estimates and can vary based on specific ingredients and portion sizes used.', '35'),
(36, 'Mushroom and Spinach Pizza', 'A Vegetarian Delight.\r\nThis vegetarian pizza is packed with flavor and healthy ingredients. Earthy mushrooms and fresh spinach combine perfectly with melty cheese for a satisfying and delicious meal.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'khbfvs.jpg', '<li>Pizza dough (store-bought or homemade)</li><li>\r\nOlive oil</li><li>\r\nGarlic cloves, minced</li><li>\r\nShredded mozzarella cheese</li><li>\r\nSliced mushrooms (cremini, portobello, or white button mushrooms)</li><li>\r\nFresh spinach leaves</li><li>\r\nOptional toppings: Chopped red onion, crumbled feta cheese, fresh herbs (thyme, oregano, basil)</li><br>\r\n', 'Preheat oven to 475°F (245°C).\r\nStretch pizza dough on a lightly floured surface or baking sheet. Brush with olive oil.\r\nSpread a thin layer of minced garlic over the dough.\r\nSprinkle with half of the shredded cheese.\r\nTop with sliced mushrooms and fresh spinach leaves.\r\nAdd remaining cheese and any additional desired toppings.\r\nBake for 10-12 minutes, or until crust is golden brown and cheese is bubbly.\r\nLet cool slightly before slicing and serving.\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 300-400</li><li>\r\nFat: 10-15g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 4-6g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 30-40g</li><li>\r\nProtein: 15-20g</li><li>\r\nSodium: 400-500mg (depending on cheese)</li><li>\r\nThis pizza is a good source of vitamins and minerals, including vitamin K, vitamin C, and iron.</li><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> Values will vary depending on the specific ingredients used', '36'),
(37, 'Paneer Makhani Pizza', 'A Match Made in Deliciousness\r\nThis fusion pizza combines the creamy tomato flavors of paneer makhani with the cheesy goodness of pizza for an unforgettable experience.\r\n', 'cbrhfsnv.jpg', '<b>For the Pizza Dough:</b>\r\n<li>All-purpose flour (around 2 cups)</li><li>\r\nActive dry yeast</li><li>\r\nWarm water</li><li>\r\nOlive oil</li><li>\r\nSalt</li>\r\n<b>For the Paneer Makhani Sauce:</b>\r\n<li>Tomato puree</li><li>\r\nButter</li><li>\r\nOnion (chopped)</li><li>\r\nGinger-garlic paste</li><li>\r\nKasuri methi (dried fenugreek leaves)</li><li>\r\nGround coriander</li><li>\r\nGaram masala</li><li>\r\nChili powder (optional)</li><li>\r\nHeavy cream</li><li>\r\nSalt to taste</li>\r\n<b>For the Toppings:</b>\r\n<li>Paneer (cubed and marinated in yogurt and spices)</li><li>\r\nBell peppers (chopped)</li><li>\r\nRed onion (thinly sliced)</li><li>\r\nMozzarella cheese</li><li>\r\nFresh cilantro (chopped, for garnish)</li><br>\r\n', '<b>Prepare the Dough:</b> Make a pizza dough by mixing flour, yeast, warm water, olive oil, and salt. Knead until smooth and elastic, then let it rise in a warm place for at least an hour.<br>\r\n<b>Make the Paneer Makhani Sauce:</b> Sauté onions in butter until softened. Add ginger-garlic paste, kasuri methi, ground coriander, garam masala, and chili powder (if using). Cook for a minute, then add tomato puree. Simmer until the sauce thickens. Stir in heavy cream and salt to taste.<br>\r\n<b>Assemble the Pizza:</b> Preheat your oven to 200°C (400°F). Roll out the pizza dough and spread the paneer makhani sauce on top. Arrange the marinated paneer cubes, bell peppers, and red onion slices. Top with mozzarella cheese.<br>\r\n<b>Bake:</b> Bake the pizza for 15-20 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is melted and bubbly.</br>\r\n<b>Garnish and Serve:</b> Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving.<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 400-500</li><li>\r\nFat: 20-25g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 40-50g</li><li>\r\nProtein: 15-20g</li>', '37'),
(38, 'Corn sandwich', 'Delight in every bite: Elevating sandwiches to a new level with our flavorful corn creation. Taste the freshness of summer with every crunchy, creamy bite. Experience satisfaction in simplicity with our delectable corn sandwich.', 'sjhbfvc.jpg', '<li>1 cup canned corn kernels, drained</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup mayonnaise</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup chopped red onion</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup chopped bell pepper (any color you prefer)</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup chopped cilantro</li><li>\r\nSalt and pepper to taste</li><li>\r\n4 slices of bread (your choice of type)\r\nButter or olive oil for grilling (optional)</li><br>\r\n', 'In a mixing bowl, combine the drained corn kernels, mayonnaise, chopped red onion, chopped bell pepper, and chopped cilantro.\r\nSeason the mixture with salt and pepper to taste, and stir until well combined.\r\nHeat a skillet or grill pan over medium heat. If desired, spread butter or olive oil on one side of each bread slice.\r\nPlace two slices of bread, buttered/oil side down, on the skillet or grill pan.\r\nSpread the corn mixture evenly over the bread slices in the skillet.\r\nPlace the remaining bread slices on top of the corn mixture, buttered/oil side up.\r\nCook the sandwiches for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until the bread is golden brown and crispy, and the filling is heated through.\r\nOnce cooked, remove the sandwiches from the skillet or grill pan, slice in half if desired, and serve hot.\r\nEnjoy your delicious corn sandwiches!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 300-350 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 6-8 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: 15-20 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 35-40 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: 3-5 grams</li><li>\r\nSodium: 500-600 mg (depending on added salt and mayonnaise)</li><li>\r\nVitamins and minerals: Provides a good amount of vitamin C, vitamin K, folate, and potassium from the vegetables and corn.</li><br><b>Note</b>\r\nPlease note that these values are approximate and may vary depending on specific ingredients and portion sizes used.\r\n\r\n', '38'),
(39, 'Veg sandwich', 'Savor the goodness of garden-fresh delights between two slices of bread. Our veg sandwich: a burst of flavor, a symphony of crunch, a celebration of health. Taste the joy of simplicity in every wholesome bite.', 'hzfsbv.jpg', '<li>4 slices of bread (whole wheat, white, or any preferred type)</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup shredded lettuce</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup sliced tomatoes</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup thinly sliced cucumber</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup sliced red onion</li><li>\r\n4 slices of cheese (cheddar, Swiss, or your favorite type)</li><li>\r\nButter or margarine for spreading (optional)</li><li>\r\nMustard or mayonnaise (optional)</li><li>\r\nSalt and pepper to taste</li><br>\r\n', 'If desired, lightly toast the bread slices in a toaster or on a skillet until golden brown.\r\nSpread butter or margarine on one side of each bread slice (optional).\r\nLayer the shredded lettuce, sliced tomatoes, sliced cucumber, and sliced red onion on two of the bread slices.\r\nSeason the vegetables with salt and pepper to taste.\r\nPlace two slices of cheese on top of the vegetables on each bread slice.\r\nIf desired, spread mustard or mayonnaise on the other two bread slices before placing them on top of the cheese, creating sandwiches.\r\nPress down gently on the sandwiches to secure the layers.\r\nSlice the sandwiches in half diagonally or into quarters, if desired.\r\nServe immediately and enjoy your delicious veg sandwich!\r\nFeel free to customize this recipe by adding other favorite vegetables or spreads, such as avocado, sprouts, hummus, or pesto. Enjoy!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 250-300 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 10-15 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: 10-15 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 25-30 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: 4-6 grams</li><li>\r\nSodium: 500-600 mg (depending on added salt and cheese)</li><li>\r\nVitamins and minerals: Provides a good amount of vitamin A, vitamin C, vitamin K, folate, calcium, and potassium from the vegetables and cheese.</li><br>\r\n<b>Note</b>\r\nPlease note that these values are approximate and may vary depending on specific ingredients and portion sizes used.\r\n\r\n', '39'),
(40, 'Coconut cookies', 'Indulge in the tropical delight of our coconut cookies, a taste of paradise in every bite. Crisp, golden-brown perfection with a hint of sweetness, these treats are a coconut lover\'s dream. Elevate your snack time with our irresistible homemade goodness.', 'hbvf.jpg', '<li>1/2 cup (115g) unsalted butter, softened</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup (100g) granulated sugar</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup (50g) brown sugar</li><li>\r\n1 large egg</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li><li>\r\n1 and 1/4 cups (155g) all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon salt</li><li>\r\n1 cup (85g) shredded coconut (sweetened or unsweetened, depending on preference)</li><br>\r\n', 'Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.\r\nIn a large mixing bowl, cream together the softened butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar until light and fluffy.\r\nBeat in the egg and vanilla extract until well combined.\r\nIn a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, and salt.\r\nGradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined.\r\nFold in the shredded coconut until evenly distributed throughout the dough.\r\nUsing a spoon or cookie scoop, drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.\r\nGently flatten each cookie dough ball with the back of a spoon or your fingers.\r\nBake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the cookies are golden brown around the edges.\r\nAllow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.\r\nOnce cooled, enjoy your delicious homemade coconut cookies!\r\nFeel free to adjust the amount of shredded coconut to suit your taste preferences. These cookies are perfect for enjoying with a cup of tea or coffee!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 100-120 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: 1-2 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: 6-8 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 11-13 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: 0.5-1 gram</li><li>\r\nSugars: 6-8 grams</li><li>\r\nSodium: 70-90 mg</li>\r\n\r\n', '40'),
(41, 'Gulab Jamun', 'Indulge in the decadent delight of homemade Gulab Jamun - tender, syrup-soaked dumplings infused with aromatic spices. A timeless Indian sweet that captivates with every luxurious bite.', 'lerhaf.jpg', '<b>For the Gulab Jamun:</b>\r\n<li>\r\n1 cup milk powder</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\n1/4 teaspoon baking soda</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons ghee or unsalted butter, melted</li><li>\r\n3-4 tablespoons milk (adjust as needed to form a smooth dough)</li><li>\r\nOil or ghee for frying (enough to deep fry the Gulab Jamun)</li>\r\n<b>For the Sugar Syrup (Chashni):</b>\r\n<li>\r\n1 1/2 cups sugar</li><li>\r\n1 1/2 cups water</li><li>\r\n3-4 green cardamom pods, crushed</li><li>\r\nA few saffron strands (optional)</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon rose water (optional)</li><br>', 'In a large mixing bowl, combine the milk powder, all-purpose flour, and baking soda. Mix well to ensure there are no lumps.\r\n\r\nAdd the melted ghee or butter to the dry ingredients. Mix it in using your fingers until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.\r\n\r\nGradually add the milk, a little at a time, and knead the mixture into a smooth dough. The dough should be soft and slightly sticky. If it\'s too dry, add a little more milk; if it\'s too wet, add a little more milk powder.\r\n\r\nCover the dough and let it rest for about 10-15 minutes.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, prepare the sugar syrup (chashni). In a saucepan, combine the sugar, water, crushed cardamom pods, and saffron strands (if using). Bring the mixture to a gentle boil, stirring occasionally, until the sugar is completely dissolved. Simmer for another 5 minutes to slightly thicken the syrup. Remove from heat and stir in the rose water (if using). Keep the sugar syrup warm.\r\n\r\nAfter the resting period, knead the dough again for a couple of minutes to make it smooth.\r\n\r\nDivide the dough into small equal-sized portions and roll each portion into smooth balls without any cracks. Ensure there are no cracks on the surface; otherwise, they might break while frying.\r\n\r\nHeat the oil or ghee in a deep frying pan over medium-low heat. The temperature of the oil should be around 300-325°F (150-160°C).\r\n\r\nGently slide the prepared dough balls into the hot oil, a few at a time, without overcrowding the pan. Fry them on low to medium-low heat, stirring gently and continuously, to ensure even cooking and browning.\r\n\r\nFry the Gulab Jamun until they turn golden brown and evenly colored on all sides. This usually takes about 8-10 minutes. Adjust the heat as needed to maintain a gentle fry.\r\n\r\nOnce fried to golden perfection, remove the Gulab Jamun from the oil using a slotted spoon and drain excess oil by placing them on paper towels for a few seconds.\r\n\r\nImmediately transfer the hot Gulab Jamun into the warm sugar syrup. Ensure that the sugar syrup covers the Gulab Jamun completely.\r\n\r\nLet the Gulab Jamun soak in the sugar syrup for at least 1-2 hours before serving. During this time, they will absorb the syrup and become soft, moist, and flavorful.\r\n\r\nServe Gulab Jamun warm or at room temperature, garnished with chopped nuts if desired. Enjoy the deliciousness of this classic Indian sweet!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: Around 150-200 kcal</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: Approximately 20-25 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: Around 8-10 grams</li><li>\r\nProtein: Approximately 2-3 grams</li><li>\r\nSugar: Approximately 15-20 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: Minimal, less than 1 gram</li><li>\r\nSodium: Varies depending on frying oil and sugar syrup, typically minimal due to low salt usage in the recipe.</li>', '41'),
(42, 'Bombay Karachi Halwa', 'Bombay Karachi Halwa: Simple 3-Ingredient Sweet Treat\r\nThis delightful dessert is perfect for satisfying your sweet tooth without the hassle.\r\n', 'shdbc.jpg', '<li>1 cup cornflour (100 grams)</li><li>\r\n1 cup sugar (200 grams)</li><li>\r\n1 cup water</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon ghee (clarified butter) (optional)</li><li>\r\nCardamom powder (a pinch, for flavor)</li><li>\r\nChopped nuts (cashews, almonds, pistachios) for garnish (optional)</li><br>\r\n', 'In a bowl, whisk together cornflour and water until smooth and free of lumps.\r\nIn a separate pan, heat sugar and water over medium-low heat until the sugar dissolves. You can add a few drops of natural food coloring or a pinch of saffron for a vibrant hue.\r\nOnce the sugar dissolves, bring the syrup to a boil.\r\nSlowly pour the cornflour mixture into the boiling syrup, whisking constantly to avoid lumps.\r\nContinue whisking until the mixture thickens and becomes translucent. This can take 5-7 minutes.\r\nIf using, add ghee and cardamom powder, and mix well.\r\nPour the halwa into a greased tray or baking dish lined with parchment paper.\r\nGarnish with chopped nuts (optional) and let it cool completely at room temperature.\r\nCut the halwa into squares and serve.<br>For a richer flavor, you can toast the nuts before adding them as garnish.\r\nYou can adjust the sweetness by adding more or less sugar.\r\nThe halwa can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to a week.\r\nThis recipe is very forgiving and can be easily doubled or tripled.<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: Approximately 300-350 (depending on added nuts and ghee)</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: Around 70 grams</li><li>\r\nProtein: Minimal</li><li>\r\nFat: Low (unless you use a lot of ghee)</li>\r\n', '42'),
(43, 'Shredded chicken pizza', 'Experience pizza perfection with our savory shredded chicken pizza, featuring tender chicken, tangy marinara, and gooey melted cheese atop a golden crust. Elevate your pizza night with this mouthwatering delight!\r\n\r\n', 'shdbcvx.jpg', '<b>For the Pizza Dough:</b>\r\n\r\n<li>1/4 teaspoons (1 packet) active dry yeast</li><li>\r\n1 cup warm water (about 110°F or 45°C)</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon sugar</li><li>\r\n2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li><li>\r\n1 teaspoon salt</li><li>\r\n2 tablespoons olive oil</li>\r\n<b>For the Pizza Toppings:</b>\r\n<li>\r\n1 cup cooked and shredded chicken breast</li><li>\r\n1/2 cup pizza sauce or marinara sauce</li><li>\r\n1 1/2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese</li><li>\r\n1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon dried oregano</li><li>\r\n1/2 teaspoon dried basil</li><li>\r\nRed pepper flakes (optional)</li><li>\r\nFresh basil leaves (optional)</li><br>', '<b>Prepare the Pizza Dough:</b>\r\n\r\nIn a small bowl, dissolve the sugar in warm water. Sprinkle the yeast over the water and let it sit for about 5-10 minutes until foamy.\r\nIn a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and salt. Make a well in the center and pour in the yeast mixture and olive oil. Stir until a dough forms.\r\nTurn the dough out onto a floured surface and knead for about 5-7 minutes until smooth and elastic. Shape the dough into a ball.\r\nPlace the dough in a lightly oiled bowl, cover with a clean kitchen towel or plastic wrap, and let it rise in a warm place for about 1-2 hours until doubled in size.\r\nPreheat the oven to 475°F (245°C). If you have a pizza stone, place it in the oven to preheat as well.\r\n\r\nOnce the dough has risen, punch it down and divide it into two equal portions. Roll out each portion into a circle of desired thickness on a lightly floured surface.\r\n\r\nTransfer the rolled-out dough onto a pizza peel or baking sheet lined with parchment paper.<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Assemble the Pizza:</b>\r\n\r\nSpread half of the pizza sauce evenly over each pizza dough, leaving a small border around the edges.\r\nSprinkle half of the shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce on each pizza.\r\nEvenly distribute the shredded chicken over the cheese.\r\nSprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, dried oregano, dried basil, and red pepper flakes if desired.<br>\r\n<b>Bake the Pizzas:</b>\r\n\r\nIf using a pizza stone, carefully transfer the assembled pizzas onto the preheated pizza stone in the oven. If using a baking sheet, place it directly in the oven.\r\nBake for 12-15 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly and melted.\r\nOnce baked, remove the pizzas from the oven and let them cool slightly for a few minutes.\r\n\r\nSlice the pizzas, garnish with fresh basil leaves if desired, and serve hot. Enjoy your delicious shredded chicken pizza!\r\n\r\nFeel free to customize the toppings according to your preferences. Enjoy your homemade pizza!<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: Approximately 250-300 kcal</li><li>\r\nProtein: Around 12-15 grams</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: About 25-30 grams</li><li>\r\nFat: Approximately 10-12 grams</li><li>\r\nFiber: Roughly 1-2 grams</li><li>\r\nSodium: Varies depending on ingredients, typically around 500-600 mg per serving</li><li>\r\nSugar: Around 2-3 grams</li>', '43'),
(44, 'Fruit Cake', 'Packed with nature\'s candy! Our fruitcake is a celebration of flavor in every slice.\r\nSun-ripened fruits, rich cake, a delightful combination that never gets old.', 'ahdbsn.jpg', '<li>Base: Flour, sugar, butter, eggs, baking powder</li><li>\r\nDried Fruit: Raisins, cranberries, cherries, chopped apricots, chopped dates</li><li>\r\nNuts: Almonds, walnuts, pecans (chopped)</li><li>\r\nSpices: Cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, ginger</li><li>\r\nLiquor (optional): Brandy, rum, or bourbon (for soaking)</li><br>\r\n', 'Preheat oven to 300°F (150°C). Grease and flour a loaf pan or bundt pan.\r\nIn a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time.\r\nIn a separate bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and spices. Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients alternately with milk, mixing until just combined.\r\nFold in chopped fruits and nuts. If using liquor, drizzle the fruits with a tablespoon or two and let them soak for 15 minutes before adding to the batter.\r\nPour batter into prepared pan and bake for 1-1/2 to 2 hours, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\r\nCool cake in pan for 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.\r\nFor a richer flavor, brush the top of the cooled cake with additional liquor (optional).<br>\r\n<h3>Nutrient values</h3>\r\n<li>Calories: 300-400</li><li>\r\nFat: 10-15g</li><li>\r\nSaturated Fat: 5-7g</li><li>\r\nCarbohydrates: 40-50g</li><li>\r\nSugar: 30-40g</li><li>\r\nProtein: 5-7g</li>\r\n', '44');

